@sriramk a) in an exponential progress curve every day is a singularity and no day is a singularity, depending on your view. 
b) in an exponential progress curve, every part is similar to every other part. 
c) no exponential progress curve can continue forever.

@almost_machines sir, a trillion dollars hasn’t gone into memory per se - but it has gone into increasing reliability, with only modest results.  

we have known about memory problems in these approaches since the 1980s; in 2001 i argued that those problems are central.

and yet here we still are.

@elijahmuraoka_ Grok watches my videos before any of you do. 

Here's its report: https://t.co/w6ob2eOHOD

And, yes, I am thinking about that now everytime I do a video.

@JasonDigitl See, that's where I disagree with you.

There's a large audience here of builders, and they don't buy the same as people over on Instagram who are more "normal" and aren't into building or development. I don't see that normie audience here on X; I see a builder audience. 

While there is a normal audience here, it doesn't intermix with the AI audience. And that's what he's getting to.

@RonnieAEvans Exactly. Adopt is the only way. 

But government does play a role in helping people out. 

Humans need years to learn new things. We need a new GI bill, which helped my dad go to college and pull our family out of poverty.

